From b4f89e4c2414b4e912409388c1fbc0489ab9dda1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 2026 00:25:03 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 017/174] PGCL: cross-arch fixes for PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4
 compilation
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fix compilation with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4 (64KB kernel pages) on multiple
architectures:

- alpha: Use MMUPAGE_SIZE for CIA TBIA workaround page alignment
  (avoids .align 17 exceeding assembler's 2^15 max)
- mips: Use PTR_LI+and for THREAD_MASK when > 16 bits in stackframe.h
  and genex.S (ori/xori limited to 16-bit immediates)
- powerpc: Compute stack frame offset in C/register instead of immediate
  for stdu/stwu/addi in irq.c, head_book3s_32.S, misc_32.S
- s390: Use MMUPAGE_SIZE for hardware-defined structures (uv_secret_list,
  lowcore, os_info, ipl_parameter_block, vsie_page, memcpy_real)
- sparc: Use MMUPAGE_SIZE in TLB/cache flush assembly (hypersparc.S,
  swift.S, tsunami.S, ultra.S, viking.S) — hardware page operations
- mm: Replace bare set_pte() with set_ptes(mm,addr,ptep,pte,1) for
  portability (powerpc doesn't expose set_pte as standalone function)

Results: 7/11 architectures now compile with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4.
Remaining: arm64, sparc64 (page table layout), powerpc (linker script
DATA_SHIFT), s390 (entry.S asm overflows) need deeper arch work.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
